                    <li>
                        a. CID Translation for FAR-15 and FAR-12: Within your returned CID file (see "CID Request" Worksheet", "Final Usage" column) please (i) identify classifications of
                        the transition parts into the categories below, and (ii) confirm (including through supplier confirmation of supplemental PO provisions) that the receiving Honeywell
                        site/supplier is is capable for FAR-12 and FAR-15 work.
                        <br />
                        <input type="checkbox"/> M, MC or OT (FAR-15)
                        <br />
                        <input type="checkbox" /> CM (FAR-12)
                        <br />
                        <input type="checkbox" /> C (Commercial)
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        b. CFDB Translation for FAR 15 and FAR 12: Within your FINAL CFDB file (see "FAR15" column and "FAR 12" column), please identify whether any of the CFDB responses in the "FAR 15" column or "FAR 12" column are "Y".
                        <br />
                        <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35548_Yes /> Any "FAR 15" = "Y"
                        <br />
                        <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35549_Yes />Any "FAR 12" = "Y"
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        c. If CID Translation responses are (i) a usage code other than "C" (e.g., "CM", "MC", "M", "OT"), or (ii) a "Y" to either "FAR 15" or "FAR 12", have you obtained
                        receiving Honeywell site/supplier confirmation of FAR-12 and/or FAR-15 capability?
                        <br />
                        <input type="checkbox" /> Yes. Proceed to question 2 below
                        <br />
                        <input type="checkbox" /> No, why? . Proceed to question 2 below.
                        <br />
                        <input type="checkbox" /> N/A, all CID Translation responses are "C" only, and CFDB File Translation responses are "N" in the FAR 15 and FAR 12 columns. Proceed to section i immediately
                        below.<ul>
                                  <li>
                                      i. Are there orders for which the CFDB Column labeled "FMS" is "Y"?
                                      <br />
                                      <input type="checkbox" /> Yes, and order is Distribution Channel 01. Engage appropriate Contract Manager to determine if there are U.S. Government restrictions.
                                      <br />
                                      <input type="checkbox" /> Yes, and order is Distribution Channel 02, Proceed to question 3 in this Section 5(a).
                                      <br />
                                      <input type="checkbox" />  No or blank. Skip the remainder of this Section 5(a) and proceed to Section 5(b) below.
                                  </li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>       
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
                2. For transitions to a supplier where either (i) the CID file has a usage code other than "C" (e.g., "CM", "MC", "M", "OT") for any part to be transitioned, or (ii) a "Y" is found in the "FAR 15" column of the CFDB file, have you confirmed with the award Commodity Manager that the quote package/response conforms to
                FAR-15 requirements (i.e., confirmation that the contract add process (AP1245) meets TINA requirements)?
                <br />
                <input type="checkbox" /> Yes.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <input type="checkbox" />  No, why?&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<input type="checkbox" /> N/A, why?
            </li>
            <li>
                <br/>
                3. Customer Contracts Review:  For the table below please answer from the CFDB output file (CFDB Final Worksheet).  Please use Column “D” for the contact information and Owners surrounding Sourcing Transitions, Sourcing Repositions, and In-Sourcing Activities.  Please Use Column “E” when performing Make to Make, Make to Buy or In-Sourcing Activities.
            </li>
            <li>
                5. For any of the Customer Contracts review sections above requiring supplier confirmation for Supplemental PO provisions or clauses, did the supplier identify any clauses they cannot conform to?
                <br />
                <input type="checkbox" /> Yes.  Part(s) will need to have a revised award strategy.
                <br />
                <input type="checkbox" />  No.
                <br />
                <input type="checkbox" />  N/A, no Supplemental PO review required.
                <br />
                Note: In critical cases, there may be a need for Customer Contract mods.  Contact associated Customer Contract Manager (see link: <a href="http://in.honeywell.com/sites/aero/LCE/Contracts/Organization/Documents/Aerospace%20Contracts%20Assignment%20Listings.xlsx"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif">Contract Manager Assignments</span></a>)
            </li>
            <li>
                6.    Customer Notification and Approval:
               <ul>
                   <li>a.       Did any of the following fields have a “Y” in the CFDB file and/or an approval or notification requirement in the Entanglement Summary: supplier change or subcontracting restrictions, place of performance, disclosure to third parties, citizenship restrictions, and security restrictions?
                       <br />
                       <input type="checkbox" /> Yes, customer approval(s) and/or notification(s) required for the transition/reposition.
                       <br />
                       <input type="checkbox" />   No.
                   </li>
                   <li>b.       Have Customer approvals and/or notifications been requested and completed for all customers with approval and/or notification requirements applicable to the transition/reposition?
                       <br />
                       <input type="checkbox" /> Yes.
                       <br />
                       <input type="checkbox" />  No, requirements have been added to the TAC 3 RAIL.   
                       <br />
                       <input type="checkbox" />  N/A, no customers require notification or approval.
                   </li>
                   <li>
                       7.  Have all issues/follow-up actions identified in the Final CFDB and Entanglement Summary been completed?
                       <br />
                       <input type="checkbox" /> Yes.
                       <br />
                       <input type="checkbox" /> No, requirements have been added to the TAC 3 RAIL.
                       <br />
                       <input type="checkbox" /> N/A, no issues/follow-up actions identified in Final CFDB and Entanglement Summary.
                   </li>
               </ul>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </p>


    <h2>Section 5(b): Channel 1 Customer Contracts (STP Phase 2 exit requirement)</h2>
    <p>
        <ul>
            <li>
                1. Within the CFDB for the parts to be transitioned/repositioned, was a Channel 1 contract found?
                <br />
                <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35563_Yes /> Yes.
                <br />
                <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35563_No /> No. Skip the remainder of this Section 5(b) and proceed to Section 6.
            </li>
            <li>
                2. FAA Notification: For all "01" Distribution parts contained within CFDB Final, transitioning or repositioning to a
                country outside of the US, has FAA Notification been submitted per AP-1612?
                <br />
                <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox62364 /> Yes.
                <br />
                <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox62365 /> No, requirements have been added to the TAC 3 RAIL.
                <br />
                <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox62366 /> N/A, transitions are within US or impact only Military customers.
            </li>
            <li>
                3. Customer Notification: Have written Customer Notifications been submitted for all customers affected by the
                transition/reposition and identified within the CFDB file? Customer Notification is identified by a "Y" in the CFDB column
                "Supplier Change Noti".
                <br />
                <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox62367 /> Yes.
                <br />
                <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox62368 /> No, requirements have been added to the TAC 3 RAIL.
                <br />
                <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox62369 /> N/A, no customers require notification.
            </li>
            <li>
